question: 致す
sourceMnemonic: Because the hiragana ends with an <ja>う</ja> sound, you know this word is a verb. The kanji itself means <kanji>do</kanji> and the verb vocab version is <vocabulary>to do</vocabulary>. This is a polite way to say "to do."
sourceReadingMnemonic: What are you going <vocabulary>to do</vocabulary>? You're going to become a professional <reading>eater</reading> (<ja>いた</ja>), because you like to do eating a lot, and you are very polite about your eating despite how fast you eat in these competitions.
